# Anti-Patterns — Contemplative Rails

> Reject on sight. Verbatim from the original handoff §8 plus FrankX-specific bans.

## In prose

- "In this article, we'll explore…" / "Welcome to my reflections on…"
- TL;DR / "Key takeaways" / "What you'll learn" / bulleted action items
- Headers like "Introduction" / "Conclusion" / "Final Thoughts"
- "What I learned the hard way" / "Three things X taught me" framings
- Generic stock phrases: "deeply transformative," "profound shift," "next-level," "game-changing," "powerful," "incredible journey"
- AI-tone phrases: "delve into", "dive deep", "it's worth noting", "certainly", "absolutely", "in conclusion", "navigate the landscape", "unleash", "harness"
- Comparative ranking of traditions ("Buddhism is more mature than…")
- Definitive doctrinal claims ("God is personal" full stop, with no qualification)
- "Quantum proves consciousness" / "Science has now confirmed mysticism"
- "Fellow seekers," "dear reader," "friends," "beloved"
- Sermon-summarizing as content
- AI-perfect testimonials, hero-journey arcs

## In identity

- Names of family members, romantic partners, children
- Name of any specific church, parish, congregation, or pastor
- Frank's home city, neighborhood, address
- Names of specific friends, colleagues, mentors who haven't consented to be cited
- Frank's day-job employer in the rails (it's named elsewhere on FrankX)

## In design / chrome

- Emoji of any kind (build-time gate via `validate-no-emojis.mjs`)
- Newsletter capture form
- Comments section, reaction buttons
- Social-share buttons
- "Subscribe to read more" gates
- "Work with me" / "Hire me" / "Book a call" CTAs
- Reading-time estimate badges
- Related-articles sidebar
- Author photo in entry header
- Links to Frank's social media accounts
- Any link to /consulting/, /vibe-club/, /accelerator/, /products/, /shop/, /collectibles/

## In SEO posture

- Featured-snippet bait language
- "Best [X] in 2026" listicles
- Comparison-table content ("Eckhart vs Ramana") — comparison is a frame, not a content type
- Schema markup that misrepresents the entry (e.g. claiming Article when content is opinion-only)

## In licensing

- "All rights reserved" footer (we use CC BY-NC-ND 4.0)
- Any pricing, paywall, or gated content
- Any affiliate link (Amazon, etc.) — book links go to publisher pages, not affiliate

## What we DO

- Cite primary sources with edition + year
- One direct quote per source per entry, ≤15 words
- Mark uncertainty explicitly
- Link to /canon/[slug] on first mention of any named teacher
- Cross-link to other rails in entry footer
- Maintain CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license declaration in JSON-LD + footer
- Surface "Cite this entry" widget — research-publication signal
- Auto-emit Article + Quotation + Person + FAQPage + BreadcrumbList JSON-LD
